<D>__{e!}
<A>__{rita picks up the largest shard of chalk from the floor and writes e on the board. she hands the chalk to precious and precious writes f. the entire class sits simultaneously and then giggles at their synchronicity.}
<C>__{ms. rain}
<D>__{this is just the beginning. why don't we try by ourselves? there are 26 letters in the alphabet. they all have a sound. these letters make up all the words in our language. please open your notebooks, write the date and then let's write the alphabet.}
<A>__{the girls begin to write. precious soon sets her pencil down, moves her hands to her stomach and looks fainterior she gathers herself, catches her breath and trudges on.}
